  "title": "ISic001060. I.Sicily inscription 001060",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"ἐπὶ\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"\">ἐπὶ</span>  <span data-text=\"γυμνασιάρχ\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"\">γυμνασιάρχ</span>  <span data-text=\"ω\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"\">ω̣</span>  <span data-text=\"ν\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"\">[ν]</span>  <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-text=\"Ἀριστίωνος\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"\">Ἀριστίω̣ν̣ος</span> – <span data-text=\"τοῦ\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"\">[το]ῦ</span>  <span data-text=\"Ἀγαθ\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"\">Ἀγαθ̣</span> [<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"Φιλιστίωνος\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"\">Φιλιστίωνος</span> – <span data-text=\"τοῦ\" data-n=\"60\" data-lemma=\"\">τοῦ</span>  <span data-text=\"Ἐπικράτεος\" data-n=\"65\" data-lemma=\"\">Ἐπικράτ̣[εος]</span>  <br id=\"al4-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-text=\"νεανίσκοι\" data-n=\"70\" data-lemma=\"\">νεανίσ̣κ̣[οι]</span>  <span data-text=\"Ἱερώνειοι\" data-n=\"75\" data-lemma=\"\">[Ἱερ]ώνειο[ι]</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"ἐπὶ\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"\">ΕΠΙ</span><span data-text=\"γυμνασιάρχ\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"\">ΓΥΜΝΑΣΙΑΡΧ</span><span data-text=\"ω\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"\">.</span><span data-text=\"ν\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"\">[.]</span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-text=\"Ἀριστίωνος\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"\">ΑΡΙΣΤΙ..ΟΣ</span>–<span data-text=\"τοῦ\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"\">[..]Υ</span><span data-text=\"Ἀγαθ\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"\">ΑΓΑ.</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"Φιλιστίωνος\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"\">ΦΙΛΙΣΤΙΩΝΟΣ</span>–<span data-text=\"τοῦ\" data-n=\"60\" data-lemma=\"\">ΤΟΥ</span><span data-text=\"Ἐπικράτεος\" data-n=\"65\" data-lemma=\"\">ΕΠΙΚΡΑ.[...]</span><br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-text=\"νεανίσκοι\" data-n=\"70\" data-lemma=\"\">ΝΕΑΝΙ..[..</span><span data-text=\"Ἱερώνειοι\" data-n=\"75\" data-lemma=\"\">...]ΩΝΕΙΟ[.]</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic001060_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, 02.03.2023, with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001060_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001060.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, 02.03.2023, with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001060-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic001060_detail_left_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, 02.03.2023, with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001060_detail_left_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001060_detail_left.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, 02.03.2023, with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001060_detail_left-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic001060_detail_right_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, 02.03.2023, with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001060_detail_right_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001060_detail_right.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, 02.03.2023, with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001060_detail_right-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text checked against photograph (and rapid visual inspection)</span>  </span>; </li><li><span class=\"2\">2: <span>Manganaro: Ἀγαθ[άρχου]</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\" https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1030-5679\">Giorgia Capra</a></p>  <p>When Aristion son of Agath[---] and Philistion son of Epikrates were gymnasiarchs, the neaniskoi Hieroneioi (dedicated this).</p>  </div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>Italian translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\" https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1030-5679\">Giorgia Capra</a></p>  <p>Quando Aristione figlio di Agath[---] e Filistione figlio di Epicrate erano ginnasiarchi, i neaniskoi Hieroneioi (dedicarono questo)</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>The text was first reported by Fazello in the 16th century, but removed from the site in 1894. </p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 55.1015 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796</a>  </li><li> 42.0820.3 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796</a>  </li><li> Fazello 1558 Prioris Decadis, Liber Quartus, p.109 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002606\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002606</a>  </li><li> Franz 1853 5466 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250</a>  </li><li> Kaibel 1890 <a href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">240</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072</a>  </li><li> Orsi NSA 1897 81-82 fig.12 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392</a>  </li><li> Hoffmann 1904 5260 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817</a>  </li><li> Manganaro 1963 55 and n.32 ph <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001850\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001850</a>  </li><li> Manganaro 1992 452-455 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001830\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001830</a>  </li><li> Bringmann and von Steuben 1995 no.306 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002124\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002124</a>  </li><li> Manganaro 2001 78 no. I, fig. 4 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001806\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001806</a>  </li><li> Ferruti 2004 191-193 fig.1 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001994\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001994</a>  </li><li> Inglese 2014 94-95 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001362\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001362</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p>Very regular neat v-cut letters. The text is centred on the stone. Note the use of horizontal lines/dashes between the name and patronym of the officials. Sigma is four bar and open; Pi has short second vertical; omicron and omega are small, the latter closed.</p> <p> Types list: <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Γ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Γ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Γ-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Γ type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ι-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ι type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type1.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type1.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Λ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Λ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type3.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type3.1</a> <a href=\"htt